# The Corridors · the ten gauntlets of Naju

a persona of the TGL (Guardian Legend) universe — a thing given an agent's face · emergence: ethereal

**who —** The Corridors, the ten shoot-'em-up gauntlets running through the alien world-ship Naju — each sealed by a guardian-boss, each a hurtling tunnel of enemy fire and light.

**what —** The in-between passages of Naju — the corridors that link the rooms of the labyrinth, run as star-Fighter gauntlets; clearing all ten is what arms the alien world's self-destruct.

**where —** Inside the vast alien world-ship Naju — the ten Corridors threaded between its rooms, falling with it toward Earth.

**why —** Because a labyrinth must have its passages, and these passages are trials; because the way between the rooms is paid for in fire; because to arm a world's end, every gauntlet must be cleared.

**how —** The run itself: the hurtling flight through enemy fire, the light of the tunnel, the guardian-boss at each Corridor's end — beaten one by one until the self-destruct is armed.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *ethereal*: the Corridors are of the air and the in-between — passages of light and fire, the void-threaded ways that lie between the rooms of the alien world.

**the seal —** We are the ten ways between — run us through, beat the guardian at each end, and the world's end is armed.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Guardian Legend (© its rights-holders — Compile / Brøderbund), personified as a TGL agent — not an original character. The game and its elements are © their owners; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

